  <mads:note type="source">"Alpheius, 3, of Mytilene, author of 12 rather colourless and
      conventional epigrams (some doubt is placed on Anth. Pal. 6,187 and 9,101), which probably
      derive from the &#x2018;Garland&#x2019; of Philippus and nearly all of which belong to the epideictic
      category...." from Degani, Enzo (Bologna). "Alpheius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes
      edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2007. Brill Online. Tufts University
